<section id="subversion-admin">
<title>Administrative Commands</title>

  <section id="subversion-admin-recover">
  <title>Repository Recovery</title>
  <para>
  When a Subversion command gets interrupted, a lock can persist on the
  database.  The Subversion repository then needs to be "recovered".
  </para>

  <para>First, make sure there are group write permissions on all of the logs in
	<filename>/misc/inca/subversion/db</filename>.  Then from the inca account,
  run the following.</para>

  <screen>
  svnadmin recover /misc/inca/subversion
  cd /misc/inca/subversion/db
  chmod g+w *
  </screen>

  </section>

</section>
